The two hills are two projecting ridges of the high plateau of the Esquiline.—Quiri- nalem: this can hardly be true, for on this hill are some of the very oldest monuments of the city, and it is said by other authorities to have been the abode of the Sabines from the time of Romulus. — inde, then, of time; deinceps, next, of suc- cession. — auget Esquilias: by increasing the population, as it was no doubt inhabited before.
